The paper deals with the problem of embedding planar graphs into $\ell_1$ with low distortion, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper also provides a polynomial time approximation algorithm for the sparsest cut problem on planar graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with approximation algorithms, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with graph theory, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category.
